===Etymology===
Speculated since the Han dynasty to be related to {{zh-l|昏|t=dusk}}, under the rationale that weddings take place around dusk. {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007: 289-290)}} notes down but is unconvinced by this semantic derivation but appeals instead to an association of femininity with darkness, akin to {{zh-l|陰}}.

{{zh-ref|Hill (2019: 219)}} would rather relate this to {{cog|bo|སྨྱན་ཀ}}.

